            bestPractices: "Always use log-probabilities to avoid numerical underflow. Apply Laplace (add-alpha) smoothing for unseen features. For text data, use MultinomialNB with TF-IDF features. For continuous data with different feature scales, use GaussianNB but check the Gaussian assumption holds.",
            performanceNotes: "Naive Bayes is extremely fast: O(n_features) for prediction. It converges faster than logistic regression, making it ideal for online learning. For large-scale text classification, use complement Naive Bayes or BernoulliNB for binary features.",
