            comparisonTable: "| Aspect | Linear Regression | Logistic Regression |\n|--------|------------------|-------------------|\n| Output | Continuous (-inf, inf) | Probability [0, 1] |\n| Loss function | MSE | Cross-entropy (log-loss) |\n| Activation | Identity | Sigmoid |\n| Decision boundary | N/A (regression) | w*x + b = 0 |\n| Interpretation | w_j = unit change in y | exp(w_j) = odds ratio |\n| Solution | Closed form (normal eq) | Iterative (GD) |\n| Assumptions | Linearity, normality | Linear decision boundary |",
            codingExamples: "import numpy as np\n\n# Sigmoid function and cross-entropy from scratch\ndef sigmoid(z):\n    \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"Sigmoid activation function\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\",\n    return 1 / (1 + np.exp(-np.clip(z, -500, 500)))\n\ndef cross_entropy_loss(y_true, y_pred):\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"Binary cross-entropy loss\\\"\\\"\\\"\n    epsilon = 1e-15\n    y_pred = np.clip(y_pred, epsilon, 1 - epsilon)\n    return -np.mean(y_true * np.log(y_pred) + (1 - y_true) * np.log(1 - y_pred))\n\ndef logistic_regression_gd(X, y, lr=0.1, epochs=1000):\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"Logistic regression with gradient descent from scratch\\\"\\\"\\\"\n    X_b = np.c_[np.ones((X.shape[0], 1)), X]\n    w = np.zeros(X_b.shape[1])\n    for _ in range(epochs):\n        z = X_b @ w\n        p = sigmoid(z)\n        gradient = X_b.T @ (p - y) / len(y)\n        w -= lr * gradient\n    return w\n\n# Compare with sklearn\nfrom sklearn.linear_model import LogisticRegression\nX = np.random.randn(200, 5)\ny = (X[:, 0] + X[:, 1] - X[:, 2] > 0).astype(int)\nw_custom = logistic_regression_gd(X, y)\nclf = LogisticRegression().fit(X, y)\nprint('Custom intercept:', w_custom[0])\nprint('sklearn intercept:', clf.intercept_[0])",
