            overview: "The sigmoid (logistic) function maps any real-valued number to a value between 0 and 1: sigma(z) = 1 / (1 + e^-z). It is the activation function for logistic regression and the final layer of binary classification neural networks. Its S-shape provides a smooth, differentiable threshold.",
            problemStatement: "Linear models produce unbounded outputs. Neural network layers produce arbitrary values. Classification needs outputs interpretable as probabilities (0 to 1). The sigmoid function provides this smooth compression.",
